BENIN – Following the alleged attacks on some top chieftains of the Edo State Chapter of the All Progressives Congress (APC) loyal to the national chairman, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, leadership of the party on Saturday warned the state government against acts capable of destroying the peace of the state. Speaking at a rally in Opoji, Esan West Local Government Area of the state, a chieftain and leader of the APC in Edo Central Senatorial District, Chief Francis Inegbeneki said the APC rally was held to receive high profile politicians from other political parties including former PDP political heavyweights, Prince Tony Omoaghe, Frank Erewele, Arc. Clifford Inegbedion among others. The defectors from the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) to the ruling party APC were received by the factional Chairman of the Edo APC, Col. David Imuse Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Imuse while receiving the defectors, noted that politics is a game of numbers, adding that “the more people you get, the better your chances of winning election.” He vowed that the party would win the forthcoming gubernatorial election following its commitment and efforts to win back more supporters ahead of the election coming up in the state. He also expressed disappointment over the attacks on members of the APC opposed to the re-election of Governor Godwin Obaseki, alleging that Barr. Anslem Ojezua, factional Chairman of the party in the state, failed to operate by the constitutional provisions of the APC, which culminated in his removal.